    "text_transliteration": "samyak yoginaḥ samādhisthāḥ | sarvatra samānadarśinaḥ | sukhī syān muktaḥ hi ||",
    "text_english": "Perfectly established in meditation, seeing all equally, the yogi attains happiness and liberation.",
    "speaker": "Krishna"
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Self-Discipline",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ध्यानयोग"
  }
]



[
  Jñāna‑Vijñāna‑Yoga  
  
  
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 1,
    "text_sanskrit": "मय्यासक्तमनाः पार्थ योगं युञ्जन्मदाश्रयः | असंशयं समग्रं मां यथा ज्ञास्यसि तच्छृणु ||",
    "text_transliteration": "mayyāsakta‑manāḥ pārtha yogaṃ yuñjan mad‑āśrayaḥ | asaṃśayaṃ samagraṃ māṃ yathā jñāsyasi tacchṛṇu ||",
    "text_english": "With your mind attached to Me, O Partha, practicing yoga and taking Me as your refuge, you shall know Me fully without doubt; hear this fully.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 2,
    "text_sanskrit": "ज्ञानं तेऽहं सविज्ञानमिदं वक्ष्याम्यशेषतः | यज्ज्ञात्वा नेह भूयोऽन्यज्ज्ञातव्यमवशिष्यते ||",
    "text_transliteration": "jñānaṃ te'haṃ sa‑vijñānam idaṃ vakṣyāmy aśeṣataḥ | yaj jñātvā neha bhūyo'nyajjñātavyam avaśiṣyate ||",
    "text_english": "I shall declare to you this knowledge, combined with realization, in full — knowing which nothing else remains to be known here.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 3,
    "text_sanskrit": "मनुष्याणां सहस्रेषु कश्चिद्यतति सिद्धये | यततामपि सिद्धानां कश्चन्मां वेत्ति तत्त्वतः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "manuṣyāṇāṃ sahasreṣu kaścid yatati siddhaye | yatatām api siddhānāṃ kaścin māṃ vetti tattvataḥ ||",
    "text_english": "Of thousands of men, hardly one strives for perfection; and of those who have achieved perfection, hardly one truly knows Me in essence.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 4,
    "text_sanskrit": "भूमिरापोऽनलो वायुः खं मनो बुद्धिरेव च | अहङ्कार इतीयं मे भिन्ना प्रकृतिरष्टधा ||",
    "text_transliteration": "bhūmir āpo 'nalo vāyuḥ khaṃ mano buddhir eva ca | ahaṅkāra itīyaṃ me bhinnā prakṛtiḥ aṣṭadhā ||",
    "text_english": "Earth, water, fire, air, ether, mind, intellect, and ego — thus My material nature is divided eightfold.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 5,
    "text_sanskrit": "अपरेयमितस्त्वन्यां प्रकृतिं विद्धि मे पराम् | जीवभूतां महाबाहो ययेदं धार्यते जगत् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "apareyam itas tv anyāṃ prakṛtiṃ viddhi me parām | jīvabhūtāṃ mahābāho yayedaṃ dhāryate jagat ||",
    "text_english": "This is My inferior nature; know as distinct from it My supreme nature by which all beings are sustained, O mighty‑armed.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 6,
    "text_sanskrit": "एतद्योनीनि भूतानि सर्वाणीत्युपधारय | अहं कृत्स्नस्य जगतः प्रभवः प्रलयस्तथा ||",
    "text_transliteration": "etad yonīni bhūtāni sarvāṇīty upadhāraya | ahaṃ kṛtsnasya jagataḥ prabhavaḥ pralayas tathā ||",
    "text_english": "Know that all beings have these two as their womb; I am the source and dissolution of the entire universe. ",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 7,
    "text_sanskrit": "मत्तः परतरं नान्यत्किञ्चिदस्ति धनञ्जय | मयि सर्वमिदं प्रोतं सूत्रे मणिगणा इव ||",
    "text_transliteration": "mattaḥ parataraṃ nānyat kiñcid asti dhanañjaya | mayi sarvam idaṃ protaṃ sūtre maṇigaṇā iva ||",
    "text_english": "O Dhananjaya, there is nothing higher than Me; all this is strung on Me like beads on a thread.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 8,
    "text_sanskrit": "रसोऽहमप्सु कौन्तेय प्रभास्मि शशिसूर्ययोः | प्रणवः सर्ववेदेषु शब्दः खे पौरुषं नृषु ||",
    "text_transliteration": "raso ’ham apsu kaunteya prabhāsmi śaśi‑sūryayoḥ | praṇavaḥ sarva‑vedeṣu śabdaḥ khe pauruṣaṃ nṛṣu ||",
    "text_english": "O son of Kunti, I am the taste in water, the light of the moon and sun, the syllable Om in the Vedas, the sound in ether, and virility in men.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 9,
    "text_sanskrit": "पुण्यो गन्धः पृथिव्यां च तेजश्चास्मि विभावसौ | जीवनं सर्वभूतेषु तपश्चास्मि तपस्विषु ||",
    "text_transliteration": "puṇyo gandhaḥ pṛthivyāṃ ca tejaś cāsmi vibhāvasau | jīvanaṃ sarvabhūteṣu tapaś cāsmi tapasviṣu ||",
    "text_english": "I am the fragrance in earth, brilliance in fire, life in all beings, and austerity in ascetics.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 10,
    "text_sanskrit": "बीजं मां सर्वभूतानां विद्धि पार्थ सनातनम् | बुद्धिर्बुद्धिमतामस्मि तेजस्तेजस्विनामहम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "bījaṃ māṃ sarvabhūtānāṃ viddhi pārtha sanātanam | buddhir buddhimatāṃ asmi tejas tej‍asvinām aham ||",
    "text_english": "Know Me as the eternal seed of all beings; I am the intelligence of the intelligent and the splendour of the radiant.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 11,
    "text_sanskrit": "बलं बलवतां चाहं कामरागविवर्जितम् | धर्माविरुद्धो भूतेषु कामोऽस्मि भरतर्षभ ||",
    "text_transliteration": "balaṃ balavatāṃ cāham kāma‑rāga‑vivarjitam | dharmā‑viruddho bhūteṣu kāmo ’smi bharatarṣabha ||",
    "text_english": "Of the strong I am strength devoid of desire; and in all beings I am desire that is not opposed to dharma.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 12,
    "text_sanskrit": "ये चैव सात्त्विका भावा राजसास्तामसाश्च ये | मत्तेवेति तान्विद्धि न त्वहं तेषु ते मयि ||",
    "text_transliteration": "ye caiva sāttvikā bhāvā rājasāstāmāsāśca ye | matteveti tān viddhi na tv ahaṃ teṣu te mayi ||",
    "text_english": "Know that the beings of quality sattva, rajas, and tamas have their source in Me; but I am not in them, they are in Me.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 13,
    "text_sanskrit": "त्रिभिर्गुणमयैर्भावैरेभिः सर्वमिदं जगत् | मोहितं नाभिजानाति मामेभ्यः परमव्ययम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "tribhir guṇa‑mayair bhāvair ebhiḥ sarvam idaṃ jagat | mohitaṃ nābhijānāti mām ebhyaḥ param avyayam ||",
    "text_english": "By these three qualities all this world is deluded and does not know Me, the unchanging Supreme.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 14,
    "text_sanskrit": "दैवी ह्येषा गुणमयी मम माया दुरत्यया | मामेव ये प्रपद्यन्ते मायामेतां तरन्ति ते ||",
    "text_transliteration": "daivī hyeṣā guṇa‑mayī mama māyā duratyayā | mām eva ye prapadyante māyāmetāṃ taranti te ||",
    "text_english": "This divine illusion, consisting of the qualities of nature, is difficult to cross over; but those who surrender unto Me alone cross over it.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 15,
    "text_sanskrit": "न मां दुष्कृतिनो मूढाः प्रपद्यन्ते नराधमाः | माययापहृतज्ञाना आसुरं भावमाश्रिताः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "na māṃ duṣkṛtino mūḍhāḥ prapadyante narādhamaḥ | māyayāpahṛta‑jñānā āsuraṃ bhāvam āśritāḥ ||",
    "text_english": "Men of crooked deeds and bewildered intellect do not surrender unto Me; having their knowledge stolen by illusion they abide in an asuric state.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 16,
    "text_sanskrit": "चतुर्विधा भजन्ते मां जनाः सुकृतिनोऽर्जुन | आर्तो जिज्ञासुरर्थार्थी ज्ञानी च भरतर्षभ ||",
    "text_transliteration": "catur‑vidhā bhajante māṃ janāḥ sukṛtino ’rjuna | ārto jijñāsur arthārthī jñānī ca bharatarṣabha ||",
    "text_english": "Four kinds of virtuous men worship Me: those distressed, those seeking knowledge, those seeking wealth, and the wise, O Arjuna.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 17,
    "text_sanskrit": "तेषां ज्ञानी नित्ययुक्त एकभक्तिर्विशिष्यते | प्रियो हि ज्ञानिनोऽत्यर्थमहं स च मम प्रियः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "teṣāṃ jñānī nitya‑yukta ekabhaktir viśiṣyate | priyo hi jñānino ’tyartha maham sa ca mama priyaḥ ||",
    "text_english": "Of them the wise, ever steadfast in devotion to One, excel; for I am exceedingly dear to the wise, and he is dear to Me.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 18,
    "text_sanskrit": "उदाराः सर्व एवैते ज्ञानी त्वात्मैव मे मतम् | आस्थितः स हि युक्तात्मा मामेवानुत्तमां गतिम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "udārāḥ sarva evaite jñānī tvātmaiva me matam | āsthitaḥ sa hi yuktātmā māmevā­nuttamāṃ gatim ||",
    "text_english": "Noble indeed are all these, but I deem the wise as My own Self; established in Me, he attains the highest goal.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 19,
    "text_sanskrit": "बहूनां जन्मनामन्ते ज्ञानवान्मां प्रपद्यते | वासुदेवः सर्वमिति स महात्मा सुदुर्लभः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "bahūnāṃ janmanām ante jñānavān māṃ prapadyate | vāsudevaḥ sarvam iti sa mahātmā sudurlabhaḥ ||",
    "text_english": "At the end of many births the wise man comes to Me, knowing that all this is Vāsudeva; such a great soul is very rare.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 20,
    "text_sanskrit": "कामैस्तैस्तैर्हृतज्ञानाः प्रपद्यन्तेऽन्यदेवताः | तं तं नियममास्थाय प्रकृत्या नियताः स्वया ||",
    "text_transliteration": "kāmaistai‑stair hṛta‑jñānāḥ prapadyante anyadevatāḥ | taṃ taṃ niyamam āsthāya prakṛtyā niyatāḥ svayā ||",
    "text_english": "Those whose wisdom is torn away by desires resort to other deities, following rituals prescribed by their own nature.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 21,
    "text_sanskrit": "यो यो यां यां तनुं भक्तः श्रद्धयार्चितुमिच्छति | तस्य तस्याचलां श्रद्धां तामेव विदधाम्यहम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "yo yo yāṃ yāṃ tanum bhaktaḥ śraddhayā rcitum icchati | tasya tasyācalāṃ śraddhāṃ tām eva vidadhāmy aham ||",
    "text_english": "Whatever form a devotee with faith desires to worship, I give that steadfast faith to him.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 22,
    "text_sanskrit": "स तया श्रद्धया युक्तस्तस्याराधनमीहते | लभते च ततः कामान्मयैव विहितान्हि तान् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "sa tayā śraddhayā yuktas tasya ārādhanam īhate | labhate ca tataḥ kāmān mayaiva vihitān hi tān ||",
    "text_english": "Endowed with that faith, he engages in worship and obtains from it the desires that are ordained by Me.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 23,
    "text_sanskrit": "अन्तवत्तु फलं तेषां तद्भवत्यल्पमेधसाम् | देवान्देवयजो यान्ति मद्भक्ता यान्ति मामपि ||",
    "text_transliteration": "antavat tu phalaṃ teṣāṃ tad bhavat yalpa‑medhasām | devān devayajo yānti madbhaktā yānti mām api ||",
    "text_english": "Indeed the fruits of those of small intelligence are limited; worshippers of gods go to them, but My devotees come to Me.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 24,
    "text_sanskrit": "अव्यक्तं व्यक्तिमापन्नं मन्यन्ते मामबुद्धयः | परं भावमजानन्तो ममाव्ययमनुत्तमम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "avyaktaṃ vyaktim āpannaṃ manyante mām abuddhayaḥ | paraṃ bhāvam ajānanto mam āvyayam anuttamam ||",
    "text_english": "Fools think of Me, the Unmanifest, as having manifestation, not knowing My immutable supreme nature.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 25,
    "text_sanskrit": "नाहं प्रकाशः सर्वस्य योगमायासमावृतः | मूढोऽयं नाभिजानाति लोको मामजमव्ययम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "nāhaṃ prakāśaḥ sarvasya yoga‑māyā samāvṛtaḥ | mūḍho 'yaṃ nābhijānāti loko mām ajam avyayam ||",
    "text_english": "I am not manifest to all, being veiled by the Yoga‑Māyā; therefore the deluded world does not know Me, the unborn and imperishable.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 26,
    "text_sanskrit": "वेदाहं समतीतानि वर्तमानानि चार्जुन | भविष्याणि च भूतानि मां तु वेद न कश्चन ||",
    "text_transliteration": "vedāhaṃ samatītāni vartamānāni cārjuna | bhaviṣyāṇi ca bhūtāni māṃ tu veda na kaścana ||",
    "text_english": "I know the beings of the past, present, and future, O Arjuna; but no one knows Me.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 27,
    "text_sanskrit": "इच्छाद्वेषसमुत्थेन द्वन्द्वमोहेन भारत | सर्वभूतानि सम्मोहं सर्गे यान्ति परन्तप ||",
    "text_transliteration": "icchād veṣa samutthena dvandva‑mohena bhārata | sarvabhūtāni sammohaṃ sarge yānti parantapa ||",
    "text_english": "O Bharata, by the delusion born of desires and aversions, all beings are enveloped in attachment at creation.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 28,
    "text_sanskrit": "येषां त्वन्तगतं पापं जनानां पुण्यकर्मणाम् | ते द्वन्द्वमोहनिर्मुक्ता भजन्ते मां दृढव्रताः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "yeṣāṃ tv antagataṃ pāpaṃ janānāṃ puṇya‑karmaṇām | te dvandva‑mohanirmuktā bhajante māṃ dṛḍhavratāḥ ||",
    "text_english": "But those whose sins have ceased and who are freed from the delusion of opposites worship Me with firm resolve.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 29,
    "text_sanskrit": "जरामरणमोक्षाय मामाश्रित्य यतन्ति ये | ते ब्रह्म तद्विदुः कृत्स्नमध्यात्मं कर्म चाखिलम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "jarā‑maraṇa‑mokṣāya mām āśritya yatanti ye | te brahma tad viduḥ kṛtsnaṃ adhyātmaṃ karma cākhilam ||",
    "text_english": "Those who strive for liberation from old age and death, taking refuge in Me, know Brahman, the whole of self and action.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 30,
    "text_sanskrit": "साधिभूताधिदैवं मां साधियज्ञं च ये विदुः | प्रयाणकालेऽपि च मां ते विदुर्युक्तचेतसः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "sādhi‑bhūtādhidaivaṃ māṃ sādhiyajñaṃ ca ye viduḥ | prayāṇa‑kāle ’pi ca māṃ te vidur yukta‑cetasaḥ ||",
    "text_english": "Those who know Me as the guiding principle of the elements, gods, and sacrifice, even at the time of death know Me with steady mind.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Knowledge and Realization",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "ज्ञानविज्ञानयोग"
  }
]


[
  Akshara‑Brahma‑Yoga

  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 1,
    "text_sanskrit": "अर्जुन उवाच | कर्मण्येवाधिकारस्ते मा फलेषु कदाचन | मा कर्मफलहेतुर्भूर्मा ते सङ्गोऽस्त्वकर्मणि ||",
    "text_transliteration": "arjuna uvāca | karmaṇyevādhikāras te mā phaleṣu kadācana | mā karma‑phala‑heturbhūr mā te saṅgo 'stvakarmaṇi ||",
    "text_english": "Arjuna said: O Krishna, what is Brahman? What is the self? How does one attain it at the time of death? Explain this fully.",
    "speaker": "Arjuna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 2,
    "text_sanskrit": "भगवानुवाच | सर्वस्य चाहं हृदि संस्थितो मत्तः स्मृतिर्ज्ञानमपोहनं च | वेदैश्च सर्वैरहमेव वेद्यो वेदान्तकृद्वेदविदेव च ||",
    "text_transliteration": "bhagavān uvāca | sarvasya cāhaṃ hṛdi saṃsthito mattaḥ smṛtiḥ jñānam apohanaṃ ca | vedaishca sarvair aham eva vedyo vedānta‑kṛd veda‑vidaiva ca ||",
    "text_english": "The Blessed Lord said: I am seated in the hearts of all. From Me come memory, knowledge, and their removal. I am to be known through all the Vedas, the knower of Vedas, and the end of all knowledge.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 3,
    "text_sanskrit": "अध्यानहृदि योगस्थः स्मृतिमात्रेण तप्यते | योऽन्तकालेऽपि मे भक्तः स मेऽन्तःस्थ भवति ||",
    "text_transliteration": "adhyāna‑hṛdi yoga‑sthaḥ smṛti‑mātreṇa tapyate | yo 'ntakāle 'pi me bhaktaḥ sa me 'ntaḥstha bhavati ||",
    "text_english": "He who is devoted to Me at the time of death, thinking of Me alone, reaches Me, O Arjuna.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 4,
    "text_sanskrit": "अन्तकाले च मामेव स्मरन्मुक्त्वा कलेवरम् | यः प्रयाति स मद्भावं याति नास्ति तस्य कश्चन ||",
    "text_transliteration": "antakāle ca mām eva smaran muktvā kalevaram | yaḥ prayāti sa mad‑bhāvaṃ yāti nāsti tasya kaścan ||",
    "text_english": "Whatever being remembers Me at the time of death, abandoning the body, he attains My state; none is lost.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 5,
    "text_sanskrit": "अथ च योगिनोऽन्तकाले ज्ञानयुक्ताः समाधियुक्ताः | मोक्षं प्रयान्ति मामुपैति चेदं तपसा यथातथम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "atha ca yogino 'ntakāle jñāna‑yuktāḥ samādhi‑yuktāḥ | mokṣaṃ prayānti mām upaiti cedam tapasā yathātatham ||",
    "text_english": "Some yogis at the time of death, endowed with knowledge and meditation, reach liberation; some attain Me by austerity, according to their practices.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 6,
    "text_sanskrit": "अशरीरं यदस्याहुः शरीरं योऽवशिष्यते | तं यान्ति परमां गतिं तमेवेत्यभिधीयते ||",
    "text_transliteration": "aśarīraṃ yadasyāhuḥ śarīraṃ yo 'vaśiṣyate | taṃ yānti paramāṃ gatiṃ tameveti abhidhīyate ||",
    "text_english": "The soul without body, remaining after the body is gone, attains the Supreme, and this is said to be the highest goal.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 7,
    "text_sanskrit": "जोऽन्तकाले मामेतं ध्यायते योगयुक्तः | स सर्वत्र विजानीतो मामेव सर्वभूतहितः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "jo 'ntakāle mām etam dhyāyate yoga‑yuktaḥ | sa sarvatra vijānīto mām eva sarva‑bhūta‑hitaḥ ||",
    "text_english": "At the time of death, he who meditates on Me, united in yoga, knows Me everywhere and benefits all beings.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 8,
    "text_sanskrit": "उत्तिष्ठ धर्मं चर पुत्र। विद्यां च नित्यसाध्यम् | ब्रह्मवादं च शास्त्राणि च यत्नेन पठतु सः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "uttiṣṭha dharmaṃ cara putra | vidyāṃ ca nitya‑sādhyam | brahma‑vādaṃ ca śāstrāṇi ca yatnena paṭhatu saḥ ||",
    "text_english": "Stand up, O son, perform your duties, constantly pursue learning, and diligently study the Vedic wisdom.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 9,
    "text_sanskrit": "सर्वभूताधिपतिं च सर्वविद्याविदां च | मयि तु कर्मणां फलं सर्वत्र समर्पितम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "sarva‑bhūta‑adhipatiṃ ca sarva‑vidyā‑vidāṃ ca | mayi tu karmaṇāṃ phalaṃ sarvatra samar­pitam ||",
    "text_english": "I am the ruler of all beings and the knower of all knowledge; the fruit of all actions is dedicated to Me.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 10,
    "text_sanskrit": "अयं आत्मा ब्रह्म नित्यम् | अनादि चिन्त्यश्च नित्यः | सर्वत्र सर्वस्य स्थितो मया | यः मां त्यक्त्वा भजति स याति परमम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "ayaṃ ātmā brahma nityam | anādi cintyaśca nityaḥ | sarvatra sarvasya sthito mayā | yaḥ māṃ tyaktvā bhajati sa yāti paramam ||",
    "text_english": "This self is eternal Brahman, without beginning and always beyond thought; established everywhere, he who surrenders and worships Me attains the supreme.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 11,
    "text_sanskrit": "अन्तकाले च मे भक्त्याऽन्तःस्थो ह्यनन्तरं योगिनः | सदा मे समर्प्यते तं ममाप्नोति परमं पदम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "antakāle ca me bhaktyā 'ntaḥstho hy anantaraṃ yoginaḥ | sadā me samarpyate taṃ mama āpnoti paramam padam ||",
    "text_english": "At the time of death, the yogi devoted to Me reaches Me immediately, having always surrendered; he attains My supreme abode.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 12,
    "text_sanskrit": "मामुपेत्य यः सर्वगं ब्रह्मणि स्थितो जितात्मा | न विजानीते कामान्न स मृत्युमुपैति कदाचन ||",
    "text_transliteration": "mām upetya yaḥ sarvagaṃ brahmaṇi sthito jitātmā | na vijānīte kāmān na sa mṛtyum upaiti kadācana ||",
    "text_english": "He who attains Me, abiding in Brahman with a self-conquered mind, never experiences sorrow or death again.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 13,
    "text_sanskrit": "अस्य योनिर्महर्षिर्जन्म कर्म च भूतले | ततः प्रवर्तते पुनः पुनः जन्म मृत्युसंसारे ||",
    "text_transliteration": "asya yonir maharṣiḥ janma karma ca bhūtale | tataḥ pravartate punaḥ punaḥ janma mṛtyu‑saṃsāre ||",
    "text_english": "From this womb of birth, the great sage undergoes actions and is born again and again in the cycle of life and death.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 14,
    "text_sanskrit": "यत्र योगेश्वरः कृष्णो यत्र पार्थो धनुर्धरः | तत्र श्रीर्विजयो भूतिर्ध्रुवा नीतिर्मतिर्मम ||",
    "text_transliteration": "yatra yogeśvaraḥ kṛṣṇo yatra pārtho dhanur dharaḥ | tatra śrīr vijayo bhūtir dhruvā nītir matir mama ||",
    "text_english": "Wherever there is Lord Krishna, the master of yoga, and wherever there is Arjuna, the supreme archer, there also are glory, victory, prosperity, and firm morality.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 15,
    "text_sanskrit": "मृत्युः सर्वहरश्चाहम् | क्षयः सर्वभूतानां च | आत्माभवेन हि तस्माद् यो मामुपासते ||",
    "text_transliteration": "mṛtyuḥ sarva‑haraś ca aham | kṣayaḥ sarva‑bhūtānāṃ ca | ātmābhavena hi tasmād yo mām upāsate ||",
    "text_english": "I am the death that destroys all; I am the annihilation of all beings. Therefore, he who worships Me with devotion transcends death.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 16,
    "text_sanskrit": "अहं सर्वस्य प्रवर्त्तकः | सर्वस्य हृदि स्थाप्य | मातृश्च पिता च | गुरुश्च शिष्य एव च ||",
    "text_transliteration": "ahaṃ sarvasya pravarttakaḥ | sarvasya hṛdi sthāpya | mātṛś ca pitā ca | guruś ca śiṣya eva ca ||",
    "text_english": "I am the creator of all, established in every heart; I am the mother, father, teacher, and the disciple as well.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 17,
    "text_sanskrit": "अविनाशी चिरंजीवी च | मृत्युर्निवार्यते हि सः | यो मामुपासते भक्त्या | स परमं पदं याति ||",
    "text_transliteration": "avinaśī caraṃjīvī ca | mṛtyur nivāryate hi saḥ | yo mām upāsate bhaktyā | sa paramam padam yāti ||",
    "text_english": "The soul is imperishable, eternal, and free from death; he who worships Me with devotion reaches the supreme abode.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 18,
    "text_sanskrit": "जन्म मृत्युर्दुःखसंसर्गो मम योगसङ्गतः | यः स्मरति मां भक्त्या | स मुक्तिं प्राप्नोति सदा ||",
    "text_transliteration": "janma mṛtyur duḥkha‑saṃsargo mama yoga‑saṅgataḥ | yaḥ smarati mām bhaktyā | sa muktiṃ prāpnoti sadā ||",
    "text_english": "Birth and death, being bound by pain, are overcome by yoga; he who remembers Me with devotion attains liberation forever.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 19,
    "text_sanskrit": "यो योगिनः स मार्गः सदा | ब्रह्मरूपः सच्चिदानन्द | स योग्यः स शाश्वतः | मामुपैति परमं पदम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "yo yoginaḥ sa mārgaḥ sadā | brahma‑rūpaḥ sat‑cid‑ānanda | sa yogyaḥ sa śāśvataḥ | mām upaiti paramam padam ||",
    "text_english": "The yogi who constantly follows this path, whose nature is Brahman, eternal consciousness and bliss, is worthy and attains Me, the supreme goal.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 20,
    "text_sanskrit": "ध्यानयोगिनोऽन्तकाले | ज्ञानयुक्ताः समाधियुक्ताः | मोक्षं प्राप्नुवन्ति सर्वदा | मामेव लक्ष्यं स्मरन्ति ||",
    "text_transliteration": "dhyāna‑yogino 'ntakāle | jñāna‑yuktāḥ samādhi‑yuktāḥ | mokṣaṃ prāpnuvanti sarvadā | mām eva lakṣyaṃ smaranti ||",
    "text_english": "Yogis at the time of death, united in meditation and knowledge, always attain liberation, remembering Me as their ultimate goal.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 21,
    "text_sanskrit": "अन्तकाले च सर्वे | भक्त्या योगयुक्ताः स्थिराः | मामुपैति शाश्वतः | परं पदं प्राप्नुवन्ति ||",
    "text_transliteration": "antakāle ca sarve | bhaktyā yoga‑yuktāḥ sthirāḥ | mām upaiti śāśvataḥ | paraṃ padam prāpnuvanti ||",
    "text_english": "At death, all those steadfast in devotion and yoga attain Me, reaching the eternal supreme abode.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 22,
    "text_sanskrit": "मां स्मरन्मरतो यः | सर्वगं परमं पदम् | मोक्षं प्राप्नुयात् सदा | योगिनो भक्त्या युक्तः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "mām smaran marato yaḥ | sarvagaṃ paramam padam | mokṣaṃ prāp­nuyāt sadā | yogino bhaktyā yuktaḥ ||",
    "text_english": "He who dies remembering Me, the all-pervading supreme goal, attains liberation, steadfast in yoga and devotion.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "अक्षरब्रह्मयोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 23,
    "text_sanskrit": "स्मरन्नेह योगसिद्धिर्भवति मृत्युना | मामुपेत्य समृद्धः | परं पदं प्राप्नोति सदा ||",
    "text_transliteration": "smaran neha yoga‑siddhir bhavati mṛtyunā | mām upetya samṛddhaḥ | paraṃ padam prāpnoti sadā ||",
    "text_english": "One who remembers Me attains perfection in yoga even at death, reaching Me, and thus achieves the supreme state.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of the Imperishable Brahman",
