[
  Rāja‑Vidya‑Yoga

  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 1,
    "text_sanskrit": "श्रद्धावाँल्लभते ज्ञानं तत्परः संयतेन्द्रियः | ज्ञानं लब्ध्वा परां शान्तिमचिरेणाधिगच्छति ||",
    "text_transliteration": "śraddhāvān labhate jñānaṃ tat paraḥ sanyatendriyaḥ | jñānaṃ labdhvā parāṃ śāntim acireṇādhigacchati ||",
    "text_english": "One who is faithful, devoted, and self-controlled attains true knowledge. Having attained knowledge, he quickly reaches supreme peace.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 2,
    "text_sanskrit": "राजविद्या राजगुह्यं पवित्रं परमं महत् | प्रत्यक्ष विज्ञानं ध्यात्म विज्ञानाद्धितिकृतं सुखं ||",
    "text_transliteration": "rāja‑vidyā rāja‑guhyaṃ pavitraṃ paramaṃ mahat | pratyakṣa jñānaṃ dhyātma jñānād dhṛtikṛtaṃ sukhaṃ ||",
    "text_english": "This is the king of sciences, the king of secrets, the most pure, the supreme, directly perceptible, the supreme happiness, and the knowledge of the self, established through meditation.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 3,
    "text_sanskrit": "अज्ञानेन हि संविद्यते कामरूपं महद्भयम् | परं ज्ञानं विदित्वा तु नश्यत्यात्मनः सुखम् ||",
    "text_transliteration": "ajñānena hi saṃvidyate kāma‑rūpaṃ mahad bhayam | paraṃ jñānaṃ viditvā tu naśyaty ātmanah sukham ||",
    "text_english": "Through ignorance, the mind is deluded by desires, which causes great fear. Understanding supreme knowledge destroys this and brings true happiness.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 4,
    "text_sanskrit": "सर्वभूतानि कौन्तेय प्रकृतिं यान्ति मामिकाम् | कल्पकृतां वयम् अव्यक्तं तत्तेन कोऽङ्करः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "sarva‑bhūtāni kaunteya prakṛtiṃ yānti māmikām | kalpakaṛtāṃ vayam avyaktaṃ tat tena ko 'ṅkaraḥ ||",
    "text_english": "O Arjuna, all beings, driven by their nature, enter My domain. I am unmanifest, beyond creation, yet the cause of all beings.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 5,
    "text_sanskrit": "अनादिं च भूतानि द्रव्यं चाव्यक्तमव्ययम् | तस्माद्यतस्त्वं ज्ञात्वा नान्यस्य कृते कार्यते ||",
    "text_transliteration": "anādiṃ ca bhūtāni dravyaṃ cāvyaktam avyayam | tasmād yatastvaṃ jñātvā nānyaśya kṛte kāryate ||",
    "text_english": "Beings have no beginning; matter is unmanifest and imperishable. Knowing this, one should act without attachment to others’ deeds.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 6,
    "text_sanskrit": "यत्र योगेश्वरः कृष्णो यत्र पार्थो धनुर्धरः | तत्र श्रीर्विजयो भूतिर्ध्रुवा नीतिर्मतिर्मम ||",
    "text_transliteration": "yatra yogeśvaraḥ kṛṣṇo yatra pārtho dhanur dharaḥ | tatra śrīr vijayo bhūtir dhruvā nītir matir mama ||",
    "text_english": "Wherever there is Lord Krishna, the master of yoga, and wherever there is Arjuna, the supreme archer, there also are glory, victory, prosperity, and firm morality.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 7,
    "text_sanskrit": "यत्सर्वाणि भूतानि आत्मैवाभूद्विजानतः | ततो यान्ति सर्वे लोकाः परं पदं गताः सुराः ||",
    "text_transliteration": "yat sarvāṇi bhūtāni ātmaivābhūd vijānataḥ | tato yānti sarve lokāḥ paraṃ padam gatāḥ surāḥ ||",
    "text_english": "All beings originate from Me; knowing this, the wise understand that all return to the supreme, divine abode.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 8,
    "text_sanskrit": "मत्तः परतरं नान्यत्किञ्चिदस्ति धनञ्जय | मयि सर्वमिदं प्रोतं सूत्रे मणिगणा इव ||",
    "text_transliteration": "mattaḥ parataraṃ nānyat kiñcid asti dhanañjaya | mayi sarvam idaṃ protaṃ sūtre maṇigaṇā iva ||",
    "text_english": "O Arjuna, there is nothing higher than Me. Everything is woven by Me, like gems strung on a thread.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 9,
    "text_sanskrit": "मच्चित्तः सर्वाणि कर्माणि साध्यं विन्दन्ति माम् | तस्माद्यस्तु कर्मणि नैनं कर्मफलत्यागं कुरु ||",
    "text_transliteration": "macchittaḥ sarvāṇi karmāṇi sādhyaṃ vindanti mām | tasmād yastu karmaṇi nainaṃ karma‑phala‑tyāgaṃ kuru ||",
    "text_english": "All actions performed with the mind fixed on Me achieve their goal. Therefore, do not abandon your duty, but act without attachment to results.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 10,
    "text_sanskrit": "एषा तेऽभिहिता संज्ञा भक्तियोगेन संन्यसः | कर्मयोगेन संयतात्मा सुखं वै च निर्विच्यते ||",
    "text_transliteration": "eṣā te 'bhihitā saṃjñā bhaktiyogena sannyasaḥ | karma‑yogena sanyatātmā sukhaṃ vai ca nirvicyate ||",
    "text_english": "This has been explained to you as the sign of renunciation through devotion; one whose mind is controlled in karma yoga attains true happiness.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 11,
    "text_sanskrit": "कुतस्त्वा कषायमाचार: पापमेवास्य जीवत: | अज्ञानं चाव्यवस्थिता ध्रुवं मोहाय कल्पते ||",
    "text_transliteration": "kutastvā kaṣāyam ācāraḥ pāpamevāsaḥ jīvataḥ | ajñānaṃ cāvyavasthitā dhruvaṃ mohāya kalpate ||",
    "text_english": "How can one, with sinful habits, live rightly? Ignorance firmly established leads only to delusion.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 12,
    "text_sanskrit": "भक्त्या मामभिजानाति यवं यतः परं तप्यते | स सन्नियम्येन्द्रियाणि युक्तः सततं स मयि ||",
    "text_transliteration": "bhaktyā mām abhijānāti yavaṃ yataḥ paraṃ tapyate | sa sannyamya indriyāṇi yuktaḥ satataṃ sa mayi ||",
    "text_english": "By devotion, one who knows Me attains the supreme. Controlling the senses and constantly united with Me, he is ever steadfast.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 13,
    "text_sanskrit": "स एवायं मम भक्त: सर्वेषु भूतेषु च | न तस्य क्रोधो भवति न तस्य शोक उपशयते ||",
    "text_transliteration": "sa evāyaṃ mama bhaktaḥ sarveṣu bhūteṣu ca | na tasya krodho bhavati na tasya śoka upaśyate ||",
    "text_english": "He who is devoted to Me, and sees Me in all beings, has neither anger nor sorrow.",
    "speaker": "Krishna",
    "chapter_name": "The Yoga of Royal Knowledge and Royal Secret",
    "chapter_name_sanskrit": "राजविद्याराजगुह्ययोग"
  },
  {
    "parva_number": 6,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 14,
    "text_sanskrit": "यथा दीपो निवातस्थो नेङ्गते सोपमा स्मृता | योगिन: सततं युक्ता भक्त्या मामुपगच्छति ||",
